## Question 6: Define Data View, Report View, and Model View. Explain the purpose of each view.

* **Report View (Definition):** The primary development canvas where visual elements are built.
* **Report View (Purpose):** To configure layouts, format charts, apply slicers, and design multi-page interactive reports for end-users.
* **Data View (Definition):** A full tabular grid view that displays the underlying rows and columns of your tables.
* **Data View (Purpose):** To inspect the data post-transformation, review data formatting, and evaluate custom calculated columns or measures written in DAX.
* **Model View (Definition):** A visual diagrammatic layout showing the schema relationship mapping of all tables in the dataset.
* **Model View (Purpose):** To establish, modify, and optimize connections, cardinality (e.g., one-to-many), and cross-filtering directionality between disparate tables.

