## Question 8: Split Owner Name to create two new columns as First Name and Last Name.

1. Open your data model inside the **Power Query Editor** (click *Transform Data* from the Home ribbon).
2. Click on the header of the column containing the name data to highlight the **Owner Name** column.
3. Right-click the column header (or go to the **Home** tab in the top ribbon) and select **Split Column** → **By Delimiter**.
4. In the configuration window that opens, select **Space** from the dropdown options as your delimiter.
5. Under the *Split at* options, select **Each occurrence of the delimiter** and click **OK**. The column will split into two new columns, automatically named `Owner Name.1` and `Owner Name.2`.
6. Double-click the header of `Owner Name.1` and type **First Name**, then press Enter.
7. Double-click the header of `Owner Name.2` and type **Last Name**, then press Enter.
8. Click the **Close & Apply** button on the far left of the Home tab to load the split columns into your report model.

